## Me
For a nextjs project which files and folders should be gitignored ? 

## AI Assistant
Here’s a solid .gitignore for a typical Next.js app to keep build artifacts, caches, local env files, and editor cruft out of your repo.
``` gitignore
# Dependencies
node_modules/
.pnp.*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# Next.js build output
.next/
out/

# Next.js/Tooling caches
.turbo/
.swc/
.eslintcache

# Environment variables (never commit secrets)
.env.local
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local

# Vercel
.vercel/

# Testing and coverage
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# Logs
logs/
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

# TypeScript
*.tsbuildinfo

# Editors/OS
.idea/
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```
Notes:
- Do commit your lockfile (e.g., package-lock.json) and Next’s next-env.d.ts.
- If you want to share editor settings, remove or tweak the .vscode/ and .idea/ ignores.

